# Project_Health_Report_Agent


Assignment: Project Health Reporting Agent
 
Context
 
You've just joined the Professional Services team. Leadership wants visibility into project health without manually chasing Project Managers every week. Your task is to build a system that provides automated project health reporting.
 
Phase 1 – Define your framework (before coding)
 
In one page, define how you'll determine the RAG (Red/Amber/Green) status.
 
Consider factors such as:
 
Schedule slippage
Budget burn
Milestone health
Blockers
Stakeholder sentiment
Any other relevant indicators
 
Clearly explain how these signals map to a RAG status and mention any assumptions you make about the data.
 
Phase 2 – Build the agent
 
Build an AI agent that:
 
Reads a project plan
Determines the RAG status
Provides clear, plain-English reasoning behind the status (not just the color)
Handles incomplete or messy data gracefully
 
Bonus (Optional):
Make the agent runnable on a weekly schedule.
 
Phase 3 – Monthly synthesis
 
Using the outputs across the sample project plans, automatically generate a 5–7 slide executive presentation that a VP could present to a client with minimal edits.
 
The presentation should:
 
Identify trends across projects (instead of simply summarizing each one)
Highlight emerging risks
Provide executive-level insights and recommendations
 
Deliverables
 
One-page RAG methodology
Working AI agent (code + instructions to run)
Sample weekly outputs for each project plan
Final monthly presentation (5–7 slides)
A short README or a 2-minute Loom video explaining your design decisions
 
